               <p>On the 15th of August, between eleven and twelve at noon, going up to <placeName id="t17760911-46-crimeloc232">Drapers-hall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-46-crimeloc232" type="placeName" value="Drapers-hall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-46-crimeloc232" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-46-off229 t17760911-46-crimeloc232"></join>, I heard some body call out a pick-pocket; I felt in my pocket and missed my handkerchief; I had it just before; it was given to me by one Hood, who took it from the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760911-46-person538">
                  GEORGE
                   HOOD
               <interp inst="t17760911-46-person538" type="surname" value="HOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-46-person538" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-46-person538" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw the prisoner following Mr. Hubbald up Throgmorton-street; I watched him, and just as he got to Drapers-hall, I saw him take the handkerchief out of Mr. Hubbald's pocket; I secured the prisoner immediately, and found the handkerchief in his bosom.</p>
               <p>[The handkerchief was produced in Court, and deposed to by the prosecutor.]</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>The last witness is a man that bears a bad character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17760911-46-verdict233" type="verdictDescription">
